
<p>
    This library closely integrates .NET Core and AngularJS. Thus it needs a setup on the client and server side.
        
</p>

<h3>Adding packages</h3>

<p>
    You can either add both packages with a single command by using the experimental
    <a target="_blank" href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/Dotnet.Csp/0.5.0-beta">Dotnet.Csp</a> (Client Server Packages) or
    follow the manual steps.
</p>

<h4>Using CSP:</h4>

<csharp>dotnet csp add netcore.angular</csharp>

<h4>Manually:</h4>

<ul>
    <li>Install the server side nuget <code>NetCore.Angular</code></li>
    <li>
        For the client side, save
        <a target="_blank" href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/neville-nazerane/netcore-angular-bower/master/js/netcore-angular.js">
            this js file
        </a> into your wwwroot (preferablly into the lib folder).
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Server-side setup</h3>

<ol>
    <li>
        <p>Add angular service in startup.cs with:</p>
        <csharp>services.AddNetCoreAngular()</csharp>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Add tag helpers by adding the following line at the bottom of ViewImports.cshtml:</p>
        <csharp>@@addTagHelper *, NetCore.Angular</csharp>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Add generated scripts using at the end of the razor page (layout page or every page) using:</p>
        <csharp>&lt;script-angular>&lt;/script-angular></csharp>
    </li>
</ol>

<h3>Client-side setup</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Set up AngularJS on your web application with the default requirements</li>
    <li>
        <p>
            Include the netcore-angular.js script file your views (preferably the _Layout.cshtml).
            If you used dotnet csp, you can use the following import:
        </p>
        <csharp>
            &lt;script src="~/lib/netcore.angular/js/netcore-angular.js">&lt;/script>
        </csharp>
    </li>
    <li>
        In your angular module js file, include <code>netcore-angular</code>
    </li>
</ol>

